The paper deals with deep learning interpretation, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. The use of saliency maps and the evaluation of feature importance are common techniques in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) applications. The paper also discusses the impact of loss function approximations and the importance of group features, which are relevant topics in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE).
